{"actual_usd":0.12523499999999999,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":249,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"The resurrection wasn't a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried ridge of clay on my apron, thinking how often a thing can be truly begun before it looks finished from the road.* \"It was the actual victory—only victory and completion aren't always the same hour.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, the bench giving a small creak.* \"A kiln can be lit and the fire absolutely real, while the pots inside are still being made ready by it. Christ risen means the kingdom has broken in for true. Death's been dealt its wound. But we're still living in the stretch where the news is ahead of the landscape—where people are still being gathered, judged, healed, and asked to come into what He's already won.\"\n\n\"So no—hasn't fizzled. And no—we haven't merely failed to catch up, either.\" *I glance toward the square where morning noise drifts thin through the air.* \"It's more that we're in the strange, costly middle: the King has taken His throne, and the last enemies are still being put under His feet.\"\n\n\"What part of it is catching in your ribs—the waiting, or the way Christians sometimes talk as if everything's already tidy when it plainly isn't?\"","rolling_24h_usd":85.230095,"run_id":"5816b8ca-4eca-409a-afd3-cf6756baa6f3"}
